<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:19PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central Greene
and southwestern Oglethorpe Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 319 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Stephens, or near
Lexington, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, Lexington, Crawford, Woodville, Maxeys, Stephens,
Penfield and Hutchings.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
